(10. Bb3 a5 11. Ne2 a4 12. Bxe6 fxe6 13. O-O Na6 {[%cal Gb7b5] In this equal
position it's already more pleasant to be Black.}) (10. Bxe6 fxe6 11. O-O-O (
11. Nf3 Nd7 12. O-O-O b5 $5 $146 {[%cal Gd7b6,Gb6d5] Black has an easy game.})
11... Nd7 12. c4 b5 13. c5 Bc7 14. Ne2 Rad8 15. f4 Nf8 $5 $146 {[%csl Yd5,Yf5]
[%cal Gf8g6,Gh7h5,Ge7f7,Yg6e7]}) 10... Na6 $5 $146 {Unable to stop White from
playing c4, Black plans ...Nc7 and ...b5.}) 9... Bf5 $5 (9... Be6 {is equally
good.}) 10. c3 (10. Bb3 a5 11. c3 (11. a4 $146 {would make sense.} Be6 $5 {
Forcing White to exchange bishops and fix Black's pawn structure.}) 11... a4
12. Bd1 Re8 13. Bf4 Nd7 14. O-O b5 $146 (14... Nb6 {The game continuation.
After} 15. Ng3 $146 Be6 16. Bxd6+ Kxd6 17. Nh5 Rg8 18. Be2 {Black has no
problems at all.}) 15. Re1 Bxf4 16. Nxf4+ Kd6 $15 {But this is even better
than the game.}) 10... Re8 11. Bf4 (11. Be3 Nd7 12. O-O {transposes 11.Be3} Nb6
13. Bb3 a5 $5 $146 14. a4 Be6 {Only Black can be better here.}) (11. O-O Nd7
