sufficient.}) 18... Bf5 $5 $146 19. Bxf5 Rxc4 20. d6 Ba5 $1 {[%cal Ga5e1,Rf1e1]
} 21. d7 Ne6 22. Be7 Bd8 23. Ba3 Ba5 {I don't see how White will improve his
position.}) 15... Ne6 16. Rfe1 $1 {when Black has difficulties to improve his
pieces.}) (13... Bb8 $146 14. Rfe1 Qc7 15. Nf4 $1 {Here is the difference
between 13.c4 and 13.Rad1} Bd7 (15... g5 16. Nh5 Qh2+ 17. Kf1 $18) (15... Ne6
16. d5 $1 $16) 16. Kf1 $1 Ne6 17. Bh7+ Kh8 18. Bf5 $16) 14. Rfe1 (14. c4 {
[%csl Gd7]} Bb8 15. Qb3 $5 (15. Rfe1 $6 {This move is not so effective anymore.
The game may follow with} Qc7 16. Kf1 ({The typical} 16. Nf4 $2 {is well met by
} Ne6 $17 {[%csl Gd7,Ge8] Now, the d4-d5 advance doesn't work since the
e8-rook is protected. This was the idea behind 13...Bd7!?.}) 16... Qh2 {
White is under pressure.}) (15. d5 cxd5 16. cxd5 Bd6 {Black should not have
problems with such a nice blockade on d6.}) 15... Qc7 16. Bf4 Qa5 {Black is
okay.}) 14... Qc8 $1 {The entire concept with 13...Bd7 followed by 14...Qc8
took me a lot of time. The idea is to force the move 15.Nf4 (Black is
threatening ...Bxh3). Once the knight appears on the f4-square, Black can gain
a tempo by means of 15...Qc7.} ({Less precise is} 14... Qc7 {when after} 15. c4
Rad8 16. c5 Bh2+ 17. Kh1 Qb8 {I am not entirely sure if Black will be able to
stop the strategically dangerous d4-d5 advance.}) 15. Nf4 Qc7 16. Qd2 Rad8 {
In this solid position, Black has several ideas at his disposal. Since White
has a space advantage, exchanges of minor pieces are generally favorable for
Black. That is why Black should always consider ideas like ...Qc8 followed by .
..Bf5 or ...Ne6. Another, more aggressive, the idea would be ...Qc8 followed
by ... Bb8 and ...Qc7. Depending on the concrete circumstances, Black can
execute one of these strategies. It is important to know that in this position
the advance c4-c5 is not dangerous for Black. For example:} 17. c4 (17. d5 b5
$5 $13) 17... Qc8 18. c5 Bb8 {[%cal Gc8c7] Black's next move would be 14...Qc7.
The move} 19. d5 $2 {is not good here. After} cxd5 20. Nxd5 Bxh3 $17 {Black is
clearly better.}) 13... Ng6 14. Rfe1 Bc7 15. Nf4 Qd6 $146 (15... Ne7 $146 {
Is equally good.}) 16. c4 $1 Ne7 $1 (16... Nxf4 $4 17. Bxf4 $18 {[%csl Re8]
[%cal Gf4d6]}) 17. c5 Qd8 18. Qd1 {[%csl Gd1][%cal Gd1f3,Gf3h5]} Nf5 19. Qh5
Bxf4 20. Bxf4 g6 21. Rxe8+ Qxe8 22. Qg4 Qd8 $1 {The position is balanced.} *

