{[#] This position was reached in the game. Sinz,B (2377)-Kvetny,M (2421)
Illertissen GER 2018. Once again, White opted for the risky 0-0-0. It goes
without saying that Black should prepare a queenside attack. For the time
being, however, White's f4-knight is very annoying. Black should decide which
one of his bishops is more important in this pawn structure.} 13... Bxf4 $1 {
This is the right decision. Black must preserve his e6-bishop since the
control over the g8-a2 diagonal is very important. Furthermore, without a
knight, White will not be able to provoke new weaknesses on the kingside.} 14.
Bxf4 b5 $1 {[%csl Ra2][%cal Ga7a5,Ga5a4,Gd8d5,Ge6a2] As we have already
pointed out, gaining space on the queenside is an important strategy in this
position. Black is ready to play a7-a5-a4 followed by ...Qd5. Of course, the
move order can vary depending on the concrete circumstances.} 15. Be4 Qd7 16.
h3 Ng6 17. Bc1 h4 $1 {This move practically eliminates White's attacking
chances on the kingside.} 18. Rhe1 a5 19. Ka1 Ne7 {This is a typical move for
the pawn structure. Depending on White's actions, Black can play ...Nd5 or
force the exchange of the light-squared bishops by means of ...Bf5. In the
former case, once again, we have a good knight versus a bad bishop.} ({
Nevertheless, probably} 19... a4 {was more consequent. Later on Black can
double the rooks along the e-file. Another typical tactical idea is ...Bb3!,
thus using the opposition along the a-file.}) 20. g3 {In order to open the
g-file, White ruins his pawn structure.} hxg3 21. Rg1 Bf5 {This was one of the
ideas behind the move 19...Ne7. After the exchange of the light-squared
bishops, White's attacking chances on the kingside are highly problematic.} 22.
Rxg3 Bxe4 23. Qxe4 Nf5 24. Qg4 Qd5 25. Rf3 g6 26. Rg1 Kf8 {White does not have
an attack anymore. Black has a better pawn structure and more active pieces.
Now, he is ready to double his rooks along the e-file. Later on, Black managed
to convert his advantage without problems.} 27. Rf4 Re6 28. h4 Ng7 29. Rf3 Rae8
30. Re3 Qh5 31. Qf4 Nf5 32. Rxe6 Rxe6 33. Rh1 Kg7 34. Be3 Ne7 35. Rg1 Nd5 36.
Qg3 Re4 37. Rh1 a4 38. a3 f5 39. Bg5 f4 40. Qh3 f6 41. Qd7+ Ne7 42. Bxf4 Qf3
43. Rg1 Qxf4 44. h5 Qxf2 45. Rxg6+ Kf7 46. Ka2 Re2 {0-1 (46) Sinz,B (2377)
-Kvetny,M (2421) Illertissen GER 2018} *

